# Vercel production deploy

Never deploy broken builds to production.

## Before deploy

1. Run `npm run build` locally and confirm exit code 0.
2. Fix all TypeScript and Next.js build errors before proceeding.
3. Prefer `npm run deploy:check` (build only) or `npm run deploy:vercel` (build then `vercel --prod`).

## Do not

- Run `vercel --prod` if `npm run build` fails locally.
- Push to the production branch expecting a green Vercel deploy without a local build first.
- Deploy with known TS/build errors "to fix in prod."

## Commit hygiene

- One coherent commit per deploy when possible.
- Deploy only code that already passes `npm run build`.

## Workflow

```bash
npm run build          # or: npm run deploy:check
git add … && git commit -m "…"
git push
npm run deploy:vercel  # optional if deploy is push-triggered; build still runs first
```

See `docs/DEPLOY.md` for the full checklist.
